django-uslug
================

A custom Unified Slug app for Django, that guarantees uniqueness.

Most of the code is originally by snippet http://www.djangosnippets.org/snippets/369/
Improved slightly to handle unique slugs and unicode chars and packaged by Val L33.

Patches welcome: http://github.com/un33k/django-uslug

Usage
=====

If you want a worry free slug-er, then this is for you.
It handles unicode and it produces unique slugs.

Here what you need to do:
        
1. Stick ``"uslug"`` in ``INSTALLED_APPS``, and then in your templates do::
   
Then import it:: from uslug import uSlug
            
That's it.

String Test Example
=====

        from uslug import uSlug
        
        s = "This is a test ---"
        r = uSlug(s)
        self.assertEquals(r, "this-is-a-test")

        s = 'C\'est déjà l\'été.'
        r = uSlug(s)
        self.assertEquals(r, "c-est-deja-l-ete")
        
        s = 'Nín hǎo. Wǒ shì zhōng guó rén'
        r = uSlug(s)
        self.assertEquals(r, "nin-hao-wo-shi-zhong-guo-ren")

        s = '影師嗎'
        r = uSlug(s)
        self.assertEquals(r, "ying-shi-ma")     
        

Object Example
=====
    Override your object's save method with something like this
    
    from uslug import uSlug

    def save(self, *args, **kwargs):
        self.slug = uSlug(self.name, instance=self)
        super(State, self).save(*args, **kwargs)

